It's time to tear down our bedroom. The last room in the house where only a little decorating has been done.
The ugly electric fireplace and the hearth have to go. We need to enclose the chimney, replace and smooth out the cracked plaster, and build the closet to measure.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch...
The dirty part of the work is done.
Behind the chimney, we found a few dried-out dead birds :(
Everything ready for the plasterer next week
The small side niche turned out well
Here comes a new closet in (but we haven't even started with the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the heating!
And we even thought to install this nice little ventilation flap so that the chimney doesn't get damp.
The chimney sweep has installed the cover and hood. Now it should be a bit safer for the ravens who like to nest up there 🪺
The plasterer is done. The floor will be laid tomorrow!
The cork underlay is laid, I've built a toilet paper roll dust extractor for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Parts for the floor are ready and can be laid. We're just taking a tea break.
Buhu. Today is progressing slowly due to super complicated cuts around the door jambs so we have a smooth transition to the hallway (where the floor will also be replaced). @user45@twitter.com has cursed me.
Done, but finally! The crowning achievement was the terrible assembly instructions for the new bed. Tonight we'll sleep well!
There's still the floor in the hallway and all the skirting boards left. The decorator is coming in a month, so we currently have bare plaster.
Some more do-it-yourself work in the evening to carve or chisel out the lower sections around the door jambs, so that the floor can fit seamlessly underneath.
The cork underlay is also laid in the hallway.
Yesterday we finished the floor in the hallway! Then at 5 AM we went to pick up item 1 at Heathrow, then a nap, and finishing touches in the hallway, the skirting boards are installed. Joints will be done when the glue dries.
